{"questionId":"17614","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The graph of the quadratic function&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;intersects the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>-axis at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The vertex of the function is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The equation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>12</mn></math> has two solutions. The first solution is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>10</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-intercepts of the graph.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></math>&nbsp;and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Accept <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math><strong> or</strong> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>, award at most <em><strong>(A0)(A1)</strong></em> if parentheses are omitted.</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"17614","referenceCode":"19N.2.SL.TZ0.T_4d","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write down the x-intercepts of the graph.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.2—Increasing and decreasing functions","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.4—Tangents and normal","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.3—Graphing","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.5—Modelling functions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}